There are some key elements of this type of garden that should be taken into account when developing your garden design. On the whole, these characteristics reflect:

Shade for keeping cool: One of the central features is to create shade to keep cool, as a way to cope with hot climates;{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/5\/5c\/Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet1.jpg\/v4-460px-Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/5\/5c\/Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet1.jpg\/v4-760px-Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}


Walls for shape and temperature regulation: These gardens are often walled and have private areas which have little association with external scenery beyond the walls. Being able to use walls as a feature piece of the garden design makes this a perfect option for fixing your existing courtyards in need of renovation;{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/5\/56\/Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet2.jpg\/v4-460px-Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/5\/56\/Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet2.jpg\/v4-760px-Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}


Water features: This garden style will usually have a central water feature, or reflection ponds; indeed water is usually at the heart of a Persian or Islamic inspired garden. (see the step below on installing water features);{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/6\/63\/Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet3.jpg\/v4-460px-Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/6\/63\/Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet3.jpg\/v4-760px-Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}


Clean lines, vibrant colour: These gardens often present clean alignments and crisp colours;{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/2\/22\/Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet4.jpg\/v4-460px-Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/2\/22\/Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet4.jpg\/v4-760px-Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}


Mosaics: They occasionally make use of intricate mosaic tiles;{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/5\/50\/Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet5.jpg\/v4-460px-Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/5\/50\/Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet5.jpg\/v4-760px-Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}


Parterre: These gardens have parterre style beds or long beds;{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/8\/86\/Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet6.jpg\/v4-460px-Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet6.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/8\/86\/Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet6.jpg\/v4-760px-Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet6.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}


Formal or informal: This garden style can be both conservative and refined, or more relaxed. The choice is up to your preferences;{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/11\/Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet7.jpg\/v4-460px-Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet7.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/11\/Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet7.jpg\/v4-760px-Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet7.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}


Archways: Arches make a good architectural theme when creating this style of garden. These can be made from wooden supports and rendered to make them appear as if made from stonework; and{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/12\/Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet8.jpg\/v4-460px-Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet8.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/12\/Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet8.jpg\/v4-760px-Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet8.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}


Symmetrical: Symmetry is a frequent requirement for this style of garden. Matching or mirroring elements can be an enjoyable part of your planning process. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/b\/bb\/Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet9.jpg\/v4-460px-Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet9.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/b\/bb\/Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet9.jpg\/v4-760px-Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-3Bullet9.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Many modern gardens or Islamic inspired gardens (the Alhambra, for example, is not in its original condition) feature neat clipped hedges as another wall concept. Some plants to consider include:
Myrtle or other scented hedges, rows of date palms (for large gardens) or any other dwarf desert type palm can be used. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/2\/24\/Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-4Bullet1.jpg\/v4-460px-Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/2\/24\/Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-4Bullet1.jpg\/v4-760px-Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Standardised citrus trees can make a nice feature, both through their fruit and perfumed flowers. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/e\/e7\/Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-4Bullet2.jpg\/v4-460px-Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/e\/e7\/Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-4Bullet2.jpg\/v4-760px-Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Bay trees are an ideal addition, as well as pomegranate trees, but it is best to keep these trees in pots, as they can be invasive. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/10\/Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-4Bullet3.jpg\/v4-460px-Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-4Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/10\/Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-4Bullet3.jpg\/v4-760px-Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-4Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Terracotta potted flowering hardy plants such as roses, lavender, geranium (pelargoniums), rosemary are all suitable features that add fragrance, colour, and beauty to the garden. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/16\/Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-4Bullet4.jpg\/v4-460px-Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-4Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/16\/Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-4Bullet4.jpg\/v4-760px-Create-a-Garden-with-Persian%2C-Arabic-or-Islamic-Influences-Step-4Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Feature desert plants such as agave, or other formal upright plants such as yuccas, which can blend in well.

text:
 Research pictures and plans of garden design examples to inspire you. The following research suggestions will help you to find good examples of Persian, Islamic, or Arabic style gardens:
Obtain books on the subject. Good gardening books will often contain many inspiring images of the layout, the styles, colours, etc., and will explain the principles at much greater length than this brief overview. Visit your local library, or your favorite bookstore. Check online. The internet has a wide range of pictures, but you need to be aware that many of the images will often end up being those of the more commonly known gardens, namely, the Alhambra, the Taj Mahal, and the Generalife. Many of the more renowned gardens are later renovations, so they may not be as true to original forms as you'd wish - it's really up to you how far back you'd like to research. Good search terms include "Islamic garden design", "Persian garden design", and "Arabic garden design". If you are lucky enough to be able to afford it, travel. Visit countries such as India, Iran, Pakistan, Turkey, etc., to find suitable gardens. When visiting these gardens, photograph many different angles to help you to reproduce your favorite ideas in your own garden later. If you have friends living in countries where Arabic, Islamic, or Persian inspired gardens are the usual style, ask them to send you photos and gardening books. Even if you cannot read the language, the photos should be very helpful in your planning. Check the suitability of your own climate. If you live in a hot climate, then it is probably that this garden design is a good choice for your location, as the plants typically found in a Persian or Islamic garden are usually hot climate types, and the shade-producing design features and water-efficient elements are better suited to a hot climate. While colder climates can work quite well, it is better to incorporate additional colour for the colder periods. See "Tips" also, for winter care. Consider the common characteristics of a Persian or Islamic garden design. There are some key elements of this type of garden that should be taken into account when developing your garden design. On the whole, these characteristics reflect:

